An [[Argument]] is valid when it takes a form in which it is impossible for the premises to be //True// and the conclusion to be //False//.

If an [[Argument]] is [[Valid|Valid Argument]], then it's corresponding [[Conditional Proposition]], is a [[Tautology|Tautologous Proposition]].
